The paper presents algorithms for solving problems related to sequences of real numbers, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of geometric algorithms and combinatorial solutions also suggests that it may belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The mention of density and sum also suggests that it may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The use of space and time complexities suggests that it may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. Finally, the mention of finding all length-constrained segments with user-specified sum and density suggests that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
